entry.def: If a liquid or a river overflows, it flows over the edges of the container or place it is in.

example.ex: Pour in some of the syrup, but not all of it, as it will probably overflow...
example.tran: 倒一些糖浆进去，但别全倒，因为可能会溢出来。

example.ex: Rivers and streams have overflowed their banks in countless places.
example.tran: 在许多地方，河流与小溪都已经决堤。

entry.def: If a place or container is overflowing with people or things, it is too full of them.

example.ex: The great hall was overflowing with people...
Jails and temporary detention camps are overflowing...
example.tran: 监狱和临时拘留所里人满为患。

entry.tran: 洋溢着（情感）；（情感）溢于言表
entry.def: If someone is overflowing with a feeling or if the feeling overflows, the person is experiencing it very strongly and shows this in their behaviour.

example.ex: Kenneth overflowed with friendliness and hospitality...
example.tran: 肯尼思满怀友善好客之情。
里德利终于按捺不住满腔的怒火。

entry.tran: （过多而）容纳不下的人（或东西）
entry.def: The overflow is the extra people or things that something cannot contain or deal with because it is not large enough.

example.ex: Tents have been set up next to hospitals to handle the overflow...
example.tran: 医院旁搭起了帐篷以安置容纳不下的人员。

example.ex: The loch's overflow cascades into the waterfalls of a Japanese water garden.
example.tran: 溢出的湖水倾泻而下，形成了一座日式水景花园的瀑布。

entry.def: An overflow is a hole or pipe through which liquid can flow out of a container when it gets too full.
If a place or container is filled to overflowing, it is so full of people or things that no more can fit in.

example.ex: The kitchen garden was full to overflowing with fresh vegetables...
example.tran: 家庭菜园里种满了新鲜蔬菜。

example.ex: He was one of the few teachers who always filled the lecture room to overflowing.
example.tran: 他是为数不多的课堂场场爆满的老师之一。
